# There are several

**The &quot;obvious&quot; way** (for most people)

    theBoolean = !theBoolean;

**The &quot;shortest&quot; way** (most of the time)

    theBoolean ^= true;

**The &quot;most visual&quot; way** (most uncertainly)

    theBoolean = theBoolean ? false : true;

#Extra: Toggle and use in a method call

